{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@badjano What did you do to generate this error? Can you show your code?\n\nA guess is you set `texture.needsUpdate = true` before the image has loaded.\n\n@mrdoob `WebGLRenderer.setTexture()` assumes `texture.image` is valid if `texture.needsUpdate = true`.\n\nThis assumption is OK as long as the library has the sole responsibility for setting the `needsUpdate` flag. However, users set that flag all the time -- and in many cases, too soon.\n\nI wonder if a change similar to the one proposed here is a good idea -- and let the renderer try to set the texture again in the next animation loop? If there is no animation loop, well, then..., that's a problem...\n","created_at":"2014-08-17T20:05:04.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5206#issuecomment-52433116","id":52433116,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5206","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDUyNDMzMTE2","updated_at":"2014-08-17T20:05:04.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/52433116","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"NONE","body":"actually I felt the need to use needsUpdate even for canvas generated texture, so that doesn't actually have an image, and maybe that's where the problem is, and I am doing it right after I create the new texture:\n\ntexture = THREE.ImageUtils.loadTexture(...\ntexture.needsUpdate = true;\n\nand:\n\ntexture = new THREE.Texture(canvas);\ntexture.needsUpdate = true;\n","created_at":"2014-08-18T18:32:27.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5206#issuecomment-52534731","id":52534731,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5206","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDUyNTM0NzMx","updated_at":"2014-08-18T18:32:27.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/52534731","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/badjano\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/badjano\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/4595224?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/badjano","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/badjano\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/badjano","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/badjano\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ1OTUyMjQ=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/badjano\/repos","received_even